I won't forget this morning in a hurry! It was freezing, the spray was crazy and it was freezing to me as the strong winds showered me continually. Sunrise didn't really happen and I was feeling like the shot wouldn't come off, I literally have 50 shots from a few comps here with rain drops all over my lens. Finally the wind changed direction and the sun poked through the clouds faintly. I had a chance to get my filters on and get the kinda image I was hoping for!

I drove for hours through blizzards overnight to get to this place for sunrise, so after all the effort I thought I best at least edit a photo and post it! It reminds me though, that I just love photography, the crazy night of driving, the mental weather and sleeping in a rocking car on a clifftop as the wind felt it was going to tip it over was all purely for the joy of capturing the images. I had no reason, no pay cheque and no agenda. That's when you know you are truly passionate about something. #iceland #hvitserkur #troll #seascape #nisifiltersanz

A golden moment this morning down on the beach. Spending time at the coast makes me so happy, so much so that getting locked out of my car after sunrise wasn't even that big a deal, ok so it was pretty annoying. But coffee made it better 😆 
#olympusinspired @olympus_au

Have a great Easter weekend folks. It's an awesome opportunity to get out and explore! This is Derwent Water in the English Lake District on a winter adventure over new year. The lakes have always been a pretty special place for me, I have spent a lot of time there. Definitely one of my favourite areas of the UK! 
#omgb #lakedistrict #derwentwater #england #lake

You may have seen in my story last week that @olympus_au sent me the awesome OMD EM1ii to play with. Its been my first time using a mirrorless camera system and I'm going to be honest I'm loving it so far! I reckon the most common question I get asked is what camera should I buy or what do you use/recommend? So if you've been thinking about mirrorless stay tuned to see what I get upto with it. My first shot was captured on the 40-150 f2.8 lens at around 100mm (so 200mm full frame) I was blown away in low light at how sharp the images are handheld. The image stabilisation is immense! #olympusinspired

I think I found my next house 🏡! You'd feel pretty small walking out of the front door every morning to that view. I captured this in Southern Iceland, it was a driving day with amazing weather all day. It was hard to make progress as me and @dutchieslife kept stopping to take photos.. good times.
